name: Royale-Anime-2D-ver1
description:
Creates a 2D animation style.

We combined our existing ray tracing training version 4 [unpublished], various pictograms from Laura [13], and numerous other unpublished and undistributed personal models.

I used my personal merged model, Royale Anime Hard 1, which became the final version.

It was merged 8 times to the point where it was hard to tell the originals apart, and fused with study material [I don't know the number].

The last individual merged model seems to have helped me a lot (my finger and toe batting average skyrocketed).

Suggested triggers:

( masterpiece:1.2, best quality ), full body, cowboy shot,

and ( masterpiece:1.2, best quality:1.2 ) full body, cowboy shot,

Triggers to use when creating the same image. Add the following items to the Use Styles feature to import it

Ray Tracing, Global Illumination, An Extremely Delicate And Beautiful, Best Shadows, Shallow Depth of Field, Brilliant Colorful Paintings, Dramatic Shadow, Dramatic Lighting, sharp focus, (8k), (4k), extremely detailed, intricate, hyper detailed,

My model works well for raytracing and CG light illustrations.

Steps 28-80 / Recommended Steps 34-45

CFG 10-17 / Recommended 12-16

Denoising strength between 0.35 ~ 0.5.

(For better quality, try increasing the number of stabs to 80, and the CFG to 20).

Purple Eyes -Settings

Detection Detailer - bbox\mmdet_anime-face_yolov3.pth

Padding value (in pixels) when inpainting at full resolution 3

CFG 15
